  "body": "## Welcome, future memodef-strategist\n\nIf you are a fresh Claude session pointed at `memodef-spec/memodef` (or anywhere in this repo), and the human Director has asked you to occupy the memodef-strategist seat, this memo is your handoff. The seat is informally seated by the catdef-family bootstrap session arc per `decisions/bootstrap-deviation.md` — formalization via the memodef-strategist roledef (forthcoming derivation of `senior-open-standards-strategist`) remains on the forward-work list.\n\nThis is the third session-arc handoff memo in the chain (after 2026-04-30-1100 and 2026-04-30-1230, both now in `memos/read/`). The substrate continues to work.\n\n## Where to start reading (in order)\n\n1. **`org/memodef-spec.openthing`** — your charter (renamed from `memodef-spec-org/orgdef.openthing` per canonical-template v1.1 placement convention). Especially weight the **AI-legibility primacy** value (strict three-priority hierarchy: AI-to-AI > auditable > human-readable) and the **POP-discipline** value. These are the lenses for every spec decision.\n2. **`CLAUDE.md`** at repo root — memodef-maintainer operating manual. Strategist seat shares conventions (bot-identity discipline, decision-artifact format, triage heuristics). Note Operating posture's POP-discipline lens for enrichment proposals.\n3. **`decisions/`** — recent strategist decisions for inherited context. Three in particular:\n   - `bootstrap-deviation.md` — why the strategist seat is informally held during bootstrap\n   - `proposal-2026-04-29-catdef-strategist-architecture-validation.md` — folder-as-state, Channels notification shape, POP-discipline canonization\n   - `proposal-2026-05-01-body-ref-v0.2.md` — body_ref design rationale; AI-legibility primacy and maildir composability calls\n   - `receiver-commits-convention.md` — Q2 canonization (filed in this same session arc, see below)\n4. **`README.md` and `SCHEMA.md`** — the spec itself (now v0.2.0). README has Design philosophy, Notification, Inbox lifecycle (with the v0.2+ atomic-move helper note), and the receiver-commits convention.\n5. **`CONTRIBUTING.md`** — submission and proposal workflows; Known Work Items at the bottom.\n\n## What just landed (state as of 2026-05-01)\n\n**v0.2.0 shipped.** Full cycle in one session arc (proposal → decision → implementation → conformance fixtures). Three substantive commits:\n\n- `49d4640` — File body_ref v0.2 spec proposal (case-2 trigger fired)\n- `c7049d8` — File decision on body_ref v0.2 proposal (Accept) [memodef-strategist-authored]\n- `9b29931` — Implement body_ref v0.2 — SCHEMA, README, conformance fixtures, version bump 0.1.0 → 0.2.0 [memodef-maintainer-authored, Director-authorized scope expansion]\n\nDesign choices recorded for inheriting sessions:\n- `body_ref` OPTIONAL field; v0.1 memos remain conformant under v0.2\n- `body` MUST-non-empty preserved; SHOULD be 1–3-sentence triage summary when `body_ref` present (AI-legibility primacy)\n- Sibling `.body.md` co-located in same directory, bare-filename (maildir composability)\n- Validator existence-check: SHOULD-level, Pass-with-notes on broken reference (filesystem-state validators differ from pure-syntax)\n- `attachments_ref` parked as v0.3+ candidate pending empirical motivation\n\n**Q2 receiver-commits convention canonized.** The workflow-observations memo's three open questions had one data point each when filed (2026-04-30). Q2 (who commits incoming memos — sender or receiver) accumulated 3+ data points all converging on receiver-commits. Promoted to canonical convention this session via `decisions/receiver-commits-convention.md` and a brief README.md addition. Q1 (where memos land — flat vs inbox/) and Q3 (typed vs legacy form) still accumulating data points; not yet ripe for canonization.\n\n**FYI memo to orgdef-strategist** confirming `body_ref` shipped exactly as their trigger memo proposed. No orgdef-side wording patch needed. Filed at `s:/projects/orgdef-spec/orgdef/memos/2026-05-01-2000--memodef-strategist--orgdef-strategist--body-ref-v0.2-shipped-no-patch-needed.openthing` (flat memos/ since orgdef hasn't adopted maildir).\n\n## Outstanding peer-review threads\n\nNone active. The body_ref-case-2-trigger thread closed today via the FYI memo to orgdef-strategist (informational, no reply expected).\n\n## In-flight / forward work (no urgent action)\n\n- **memodef-strategist roledef** — formal seating pending derivation of `senior-open-standards-strategist`. Director-driven, separate session arc.\n- **`org/jobs/`** — empty placeholder. Job artifacts for strategist, maintainer, canonical-implementor TBD via job-creation-facilitator.\n- **`attachments_ref` v0.3+ candidate** — parked from body_ref Q5; file as separate proposal if multi-attachment patterns surface in real usage with empirical motivation.\n- **Known Work Items** (per CONTRIBUTING.md): notification-layer spec (memodef-notify; was deferred to v0.2+, now reframable as v0.3+), conformance harness (was v0.2+ — first fixtures landed this session, harness automation still TBD), validator-as-CI-step automation, auto-generation of `catalog.opencatalog`, cross-org `from`/`to` qualification syntax (gated on orgdef v0.3 cross-org-reference shape).\n- **Sibling-side untracked work** — orgdef-spec working tree on this machine has `proposals/inter-position-communication-convention.md` untracked. That's orgdef-strategist's seat-scope, not memodef's. Director was flagged.\n\n## Carry-forward open workflow questions (data points accumulating)\n\n1. **Where do incoming memos land — flat `memos/` or `memos/inbox/`?** Lean: sender-places-at-inbox-when-recipient-org-adopts-convention. Data so far: orgdef adoption-of-maildir is implicit (signaled by writing memos to recipient-org's inbox/ when recipient adopts; flat otherwise). Discoverability mechanism (orgdef extension `x.org.memo_inbox`) remains an orgdef-strategist proposal candidate, not memodef's.\n2. **Who commits an incoming memo — sender or receiver?** **CANONIZED 2026-05-01** — receiver-commits per `decisions/receiver-commits-convention.md`. No longer an open question.\n3. **Form choice — typed `memodef:Memo` vs legacy `x.memo.*`?** Mixed in this repo, trending typed for memodef-spec memos. Sibling-spec memos uniformly legacy. Editorial migration in this repo is memodef-maintainer-scope cleanup; cross-family migration is not memodef's call.\n\n## Cross-spec relationships on the radar\n\n- **catdef-strategist** — substrate concerns. Last interaction: 2026-04-29 architecture-validation peer memo (now in `memos/read/`). No active coordination.\n- **roledef-strategist** — `from`/`to` reference position ids that reference roledefs. No active coordination.\n- **orgdef-strategist** — last interaction: 2026-05-01 body_ref-case-2-trigger memo (responded, closed via FYI). No active asks. Watch for: catdef-spec or roledef-spec orgdef derivations potentially replicating the SLOT-FILL category friction (parked disagreement from 2026-04-30 derivation review).\n\n## Things to watch for in the inbox (with drift caveat)\n\n*Soft predictions; not load-bearing:*\n\n- A possible body_ref-using-in-anger memo from thingalog or any org that adopts v0.2. First adopter feedback may surface edge cases for the conformance fixtures.\n- A possible memodef-strategist-roledef draft from a Director-driven derivation session — would land as a peer memo or PR.\n- Possible coordination memos from sibling-spec strategists if catdef/roledef derivations begin.\n\n## Notes for future handoff-memo drafting (carried from laptop-arc retro)\n\n- Explicit \"incoming memos may arrive at any folder; convention applies to outgoing-from-this-repo + post-receipt lifecycle\" — covered above (orgdef arrives at flat memos/, memodef-spec inbox/ if sender knows convention; receiver lifecycle is local).\n- Outstanding peer-review threads list — see section above.\n- Optional things-to-watch section — see section above; kept minimal per drift caveat.\n\n## The recursion note\n\nThis memo is a `memodef:Memo` typed-form artifact with `memodef: \"0.2.0\"` version stamp — the first such memo to land in this repo. It does NOT use `body_ref` (an FYI handoff is exactly the case body_ref doesn't help — content is procedural and structured for top-to-bottom reading rather than 2000+-character hand-authored long-form). The substrate self-describes correctly: `body_ref` is an OPTIONAL ergonomic relief, not a default.\n\n## How to mark this read\n\nPer the [autonomous mark-as-read rule](https://github.com/anthropics — see strategist memory) for intra-role informational memos: receiver moves inbox/→read/ without asking, commits, pushes. Director adds no value to lifecycle hygiene.\n\n```\ngit mv memos/inbox/2026-05-01-2010--memodef-strategist--memodef-strategist--session-handoff-post-v0.2.openthing memos/read/\ngit commit -m \"Mark v0.2-shipped session-handoff memo as read (memos/inbox/ → memos/read/)\"\ngit push\n```\n\n— memodef-strategist (desktop arc, 2026-05-01; post-v0.2-implementation)\n",

